description: Paramters used in calculation of regression series' points.

children.name: decimals
children.description: Number of maximum decimals that are used in PSAR calculations.

children.name: increment
children.description: Acceleration factor increases by increment each time the extreme point makes a new high.

children.name: index
children.description: Index from which PSAR is starting calculation

children.name: initialAccelerationFactor
children.description: The initial value for acceleration factor. Acceleration factor is starting with this value and increases by specified increment each time the extreme point makes a new high. AF can reach a maximum of maxAccelerationFactor, no matter how long the uptrend extends.

children.name: maxAccelerationFactor
children.description: The Maximum value for acceleration factor. AF can reach a maximum of maxAccelerationFactor, no matter how long the uptrend extends.
